JOHANNESBURG - Swedish media on Thursday reported legendary Swedish DJ and producer Avicci took his own life. The electro-dance sensation, whose real name was Tim Bergling, was found dead last week. WATCH: DJs Fresh, Euphonik hail Avicii as a pioneer in the industry Aftonbladet published an open letter from the late DJ's family on Thursday in which they say: “Our beloved Tim was a seeker, a fragile artistic soul searching for answers to existential questions. An over-achieving perfectionist who travelled and worked hard at a pace that led to extreme stress." The family goes on to say: "He really struggled with thoughts about meaning, life, happiness. He could not go on any longer. He wanted to find peace." READ: Avicii death a coming-of-age in electronic music boom A police source in Oman, where Avicii was found dead, last week said there was no suspicion of criminal activity following the artist’s death. eNCA